{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Index"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":"? { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"index","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The position of the element to access."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returning ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"range simply result in ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example usage:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, ","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Accesses the element at the specified position in a safe manner."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection\/subscript(safe:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:Sl11SwiftExtrasE4safe7ElementQzSg5IndexQz_tcip","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Subscript","symbolKind":"subs